Each `Card` object has a unique `Id` and a `Units` property to keep track of the card's unit count. The `Timestamp` property stores the time the card was created, while the `UsageTimestamp` property stores the time the card was last used. 

Note that the `UsageTimestamp` property is not required by the problem statement, but it may be useful in keeping track of user activity or card usage patterns. 

